      "writtenOn": "2020-01-21T07:57:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "While this type is used generally to abstract exec.Cmd, it is used only for *_test_runner for now. How about naming it runnerCmd to make it explicit?\n\nOtherwise, in appearance of cmd like \"func foo(r cmd) error\", it\u0027s not clear what r is for (e.g. I wonder if it is possible that cmd is for bundle executables). It can be resolved either by (1) naming variables explicitly, i.e. \"func foo(runner cmd) error\", or (2) naming the type explicitly, i.e. \"func foo(r runnerCmd) error\". I personally prefer the second choice.",
      "range": {
